**[1847, 03-31] Ms.A.1.2.17.27**

RDW to WLG

Re: Douglass. “He has borne himself with wonderful steadiness & has been
as true as steel to the banner under which he fights. I admire and
respect him highly, but he is not one of those with whom I have been
able to feel much freedom. You are twenty times a pleasanter body …
Considering what Douglass has been, it is perfectly wonderful that he is
what he is. …


